The paper deals with information theory, cryptography, and communication complexity, which are all relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with mutual information and secret key agreement protocols. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also likely as the paper deals with shared secret keys and the security of protocols. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper deals with complexity profiles and tuples of strings. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper deals with communication complexity. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is less likely but still relevant as the paper deals with protocols with interaction on a public channel.
